Sentencas: The anode-supported solid state fuel cells were fabricated by tape-casting and co-sintering techniques.
Titulo: Effect of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)0.95MnO3 current-collecting layer on the stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)(0.95)MnO3 (LSM95) current-collecting layer at the cathode side on the electrochemical stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells were investigated.
Titulo: Effect of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)0.95MnO3 current-collecting layer on the stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The assembled cell was electrochemically characterized from 800 to 700 degrees C with humidified H-2 as fuel and O-2 as oxidant.
Titulo: Effect of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)0.95MnO3 current-collecting layer on the stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The open circuit voltages decreased with decreasing temperature which were opposite from the results calculated from the Nernst equation for each temperature, and the values were 1.14, 1.09 and 1.03 Vat 800, 750 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)0.95MnO3 current-collecting layer on the stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: EDX analysis revealed that Ag diffused from the cathode current-collecting layer to the surface of electrolyte which was caused by Ag electromigration under current.
Titulo: Effect of Ag-(La0.8Sr0.2)0.95MnO3 current-collecting layer on the stability of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The phenomenon of Ag electromigration led to unstable cell performance during long-time operation.
